description: Rebuild Docker images after backend or compose changes under server/
globs:
  - server/**
alwaysApply: false
---

# WheelSense Server And Docker

When you change anything under `server/` that affects runtime behavior, treat the task as incomplete until the relevant Docker service has been rebuilt.

Default verification command:

```bash
cd server
docker compose up -d --build wheelsense-platform-server
```

If the change also affects the Dockerized frontend:

```bash
cd server
docker compose up -d --build wheelsense-platform-server wheelsense-platform-web
```

This rule is aligned with the current Docker guidance in:

- `server/AGENTS.md`
- `server/docs/RUNBOOK.md`
